<subSubSection pageId="67" pageNumber="68" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="67.[151,1436,330,715]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,273,366,391]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">Notes.</emphasis>
A male from Monroe Co. was identified by T.B. Mitchell, although he did not include Michigan in the speciesâ€™ range in his 1960 revision. 
<bibRefCitation author="Stephen" box="[574,749,402,427]" firstAuthor="Stephen" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" pagination="149 - 527" refId="ref103403" refString="Stephen, W. P. (1954) A revision of the bee genus Colletes in America North of Mexico. The University of Kansas Science Bulletin, 36, 149 - 527." type="journal article" year="1954">Stephen (1954)</bibRefCitation>
lists Carlinville, Illinois as the westernmost locality for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Patton" authorityYear="1879" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aestivalis">
<emphasis box="[1410,1429,403,426]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[151,257,438,463]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">aestivalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, whereas the closely related species 
<taxonomicName authority="Cockerell" authorityName="Cockerell" authorityYear="1906" box="[692,950,438,463]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="andrewsi">
<emphasis box="[692,711,439,462]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[729,830,438,463]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">andrewsi</emphasis>
Cockerell
</taxonomicName>
occurs as far east as Wisconsin (
<bibRefCitation author="Wolf &amp; Ascher" firstAuthor="Wolf" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" pagination="129 - 168" refId="ref106106" refString="Wolf, A. T. &amp; Ascher, J. S. (2009) Bees of Wisconsin (Hymenoptera: Apoidea: Anthophila). The Great Lakes Entomologist, 41, 129 - 168." type="journal article" year="2009">Wolf &amp; Ascher, 2009</bibRefCitation>
). Both are oligolectic on 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[600,710,474,499]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Saxifragaceae" genus="Heuchera" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[600,710,474,499]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">Heuchera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp. (
<taxonomicName box="[783,947,474,499]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Saxifragaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Saxifragaceae</taxonomicName>
). Identification of the two specimens from southeast Michigan reported below as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Patton" authorityYear="1879" box="[600,706,510,535]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aestivalis">
<emphasis box="[600,706,510,535]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">aestivalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was confirmed by JG based on the relative length of the hind basitarsus (
<bibRefCitation author="Stephen" box="[276,431,546,571]" firstAuthor="Stephen" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" pagination="149 - 527" refId="ref103403" refString="Stephen, W. P. (1954) A revision of the bee genus Colletes in America North of Mexico. The University of Kansas Science Bulletin, 36, 149 - 527." type="journal article" year="1954">Stephen 1954</bibRefCitation>
) and reference to comparative material of that species from more eastern localities. There are very few recent records of 
<taxonomicName authority="Patton" authorityName="Patton" authorityYear="1879" box="[489,706,582,607]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aestivalis">
<emphasis box="[489,508,583,606]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[522,628,582,607]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">aestivalis</emphasis>
Patton
</taxonomicName>
and none from Michigan or, to our knowledge, from anywhere in the Northeastern United States. We therefore regard it as being of conservation concern.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
